  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Mangkhut Affected LGUs in designing high priority WaSH projects</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A workshop for local Water and Sanitation actors  of two municipalities affected by Typhoon Mangkhut (engineers and local government staff) to build their capacity in developing project designs and proposals for water system expansion and development. Apart from the post-disaster context, it is also done while El Nino is predicted to extend the dry season in the areas.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Continued programming for Zero Open Defecation and expansion of water systems</narrative>
  </description>
